(Picture: Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A man was severely burnt on Monday after he pulled his clothing out of a transformer box, which then exploded and caught fire, in Weltevreden, west of Johannesburg, paramedics said.The 35-year-old man was in a critical condition, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said.Paramedics found he had sustained severe burns over most of his body in the early evening.He was given advanced life support to stabilise his vital signs.Once stable, he was taken to Helen Joseph Hospital for further treatment."Witnesses on scene told paramedics that they had seen the man pulling some clothes out of the transformer box before it caught fire," Meiring said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.